parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator can cause the engine to overheat, leading to costly repairs, engine damage, or even engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Coolant leaks
overheating engine
loss of coolant
cracked or fractured radiator
radiator replacement
coolant odor in the vehicle interior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or lunge forward, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

jerks
or lunges forward when shifting gears
feels like being hit from behind

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
